10:09.960 --> 10:16.680
Our American way of living promotes incentive for every individual. The person who works harder

10:16.680 --> 10:24.120
or does a better job receives extra benefit. Those who produce more get more and this we believe

10:24.120 --> 10:31.800
is a just reward. There is the danger however of any of us establishing a distorted sense of value.

10:32.680 --> 10:39.960
We sometimes become so in growth in gaining material benefits that we forget such important

10:39.960 --> 10:47.320
items as religion, culture, family and even our own physical well-being and even if we do not forget

10:47.320 --> 10:53.960
them we neglect. One of the questions we must face is whether or not we have in the last two

10:53.960 --> 11:03.960
decades gained a new leisure time only to spend it somewhat unwiz. Recreation is God's great

11:03.960 --> 11:12.440
out of doors prescription. It is a prescription for you and me and one which doctors often prescribe

11:12.440 --> 11:19.640
not only for us but for themselves. The value of a day and Tennessee's magnificent outdoors

11:20.120 --> 11:27.320
or on one of our fine lakes and streams is something that cannot be overestimated.

11:27.320 --> 11:32.840
It is conservatively estimated that some 25% of all Tennessee's,

11:32.840 --> 11:42.120
hunt or fish or do boat, perhaps a greater percentage than participate in any other form of recreation.

11:42.120 --> 11:48.760
The recreations of hunting and fishing are of course depended upon the wildlife resources of our state.

11:48.920 --> 11:55.400
The many forms of wildlife in turn are dependent upon conservation practices being applied to our

11:55.400 --> 12:03.320
soils, our waters and our forests. Thus in order to call attention to the need for continued

12:03.320 --> 12:11.480
application of proper soil forestry water and wildlife conservation practices this proclamation

12:11.480 --> 12:19.240
has been prepared. Whereas hunting, fishing and trapping play important roles in the initial

12:19.240 --> 12:27.240
exploration and subsequent development of Tennessee. And whereas the wildlife resources upon which

12:27.240 --> 12:33.080
these wholesome and healthful recreations are dependent continue to be of great aesthetic and

12:33.080 --> 12:39.560
economic value to young and old Tennisians alive. In whereas citizens of this age,

12:39.560 --> 12:46.440
bear an obligation to future generations to perpetuate the multitudinous values of the aforementioned

12:46.440 --> 12:52.840
wildlife resources. Now therefore, I Frank G. Clemmet, governor of the state of Tennessee,

12:52.840 --> 13:01.720
do hereby proclaim and to set aside the week of March 20 through March 26, 1955 to be observed

13:01.720 --> 13:08.920
throughout the sovereign state as wildlife restoration week. And witness where I have here

13:08.920 --> 13:16.200
unto set my hand and calls to be a fix the great seal of the state of Tennessee and the capital

13:16.200 --> 13:21.240
and the city of Nashville this first day of March 1955.

