14:10.520 --> 14:18.360
most valuable forms of wildlife, ducks, geese, songbirds, fur bearers and fish. State and federal

14:18.360 --> 14:25.000
conservation agencies are initiating programs for the preservation of remaining wetlands. The

14:25.000 --> 14:31.720
health band support of every Tennessee and its require if these resources are to be saved. Let's

14:31.720 --> 14:38.680
do a little work, have a little fun and make not only our pleasure but the pleasure of our children

14:38.680 --> 14:43.720
and our children's children and the great outdoor life of greater and more secure.

16:19.320 --> 16:34.600
Ladies and gentlemen, this is Estes' key fover candidate for re-election to a second term in the

16:34.600 --> 16:41.320
United States Senate speaking to you on this occasion. On this occasion I want to talk with you about

16:41.320 --> 16:47.640
the importance of agriculture and the position that I have taken during the 15 and a half years that

16:47.640 --> 16:53.720
I have been either in the Congress or in the United States Senate in connection with our agricultural

16:53.720 --> 17:00.680
problems. I feel that the farmers are the backbone of this nation. We cannot have prosperity either

17:00.680 --> 17:07.560
for our industry or for our working people unless the farmers do well. So I have always thought to work

17:07.560 --> 17:14.360
far and sponsor and secure the passage of programs that would give the farmer an even break with

17:14.360 --> 17:20.920
labor and with industry. I think that all of these great segments of our economy must do well

17:20.920 --> 17:26.600
if the nation is going to go forward and prosper. If the farmer doesn't do well the other two cannot

17:27.800 --> 17:33.960
industry cannot have things cannot manufacture things and people are out of work in the various

17:33.960 --> 17:39.720
plants of this nation. We have in the nation today some protection for industry and the way of

17:39.720 --> 17:46.600
protective tariffs and other protections and that's all right up to a point and we have a

17:46.600 --> 17:53.080
floor under wages and then salaries and wages are fixed back, collective bargaining and I believe in

17:53.080 --> 17:57.880
collective bargaining and I believe in good wages for our working people. But you simply cannot

17:57.880 --> 18:04.040
protect two segments of our economy and throw the farmer to the four wins. The farmer is entitled to

18:04.120 --> 18:11.640
be treated on a parity or an inequality with industry and with labor so that I have always thought to

18:11.640 --> 18:18.360
try to see that the farmer got prices for his products which would give him an equivalent

18:18.360 --> 18:24.760
purchasing power and place in our economy with these other two sections. I have always thought for

18:24.760 --> 18:31.000
90% of parity as a support price for farmers products. I know it may not be the ultimate answer

18:31.480 --> 18:37.080
but until some other method of is arrived at which will keep farmers prices up and will not

18:38.120 --> 18:44.360
discriminate against the farmer I'm going to continue to support 90% of parity. As a matter of

18:44.360 --> 18:48.920
fact I have a bill pending in the Senate now which I expect to offer when the agricultural

18:48.920 --> 18:55.000
program comes up soon in the United States Senate which will continue this program on for another

18:55.000 --> 19:00.520
two years. I'm certain that one of the reasons why we are having unemployment in the nation today

19:01.400 --> 19:08.760
and why there is somewhat of a recession is the fact that farmers prices have been going down and

19:08.760 --> 19:17.480
down more than 23 or 4% whereas everything the farmer has to buy has been staying up high or even

19:17.480 --> 19:27.400
going higher. During the month of May and June for instance parity fell from 92 to 88% whereas the

19:27.400 --> 19:33.960
price of steel has gone up for about $3. Well that just isn't fair to the farmer it's not a good

19:33.960 --> 19:40.040
thing for the nation and I think we ought to try to do something about it. In the Senate sometime

19:40.040 --> 19:45.080
back I have co-sponsored the so-called fire amendment to try to give some protection to our dairy

19:45.080 --> 19:51.960
farmers. This fire amendment provided that 90% support price on dairy products could not be lowered

19:52.520 --> 19:57.640
unless there was a corresponding decrease in lowering of the things that dairy farmers had to buy.

19:58.280 --> 20:02.680
We were not successful in getting the amendment by but we tried and we will try again.

20:03.640 --> 20:08.120
I know that we do have a substantial surplus in the nation but if we would get more of it in our

20:08.120 --> 20:14.360
school lunch program if we would open up the gates of world trade and sell things abroad and take

20:14.360 --> 20:20.360
things back from other nations that we need we wouldn't have any farm surplus. That would be a

20:20.360 --> 20:26.520
good thing for our agriculture for our industry and in the interest of peace too and I hope that we

20:26.520 --> 20:33.720
can get such a reciprocal trade program through on a long and permanent basis. Thank you very much.

