26:26.920 --> 26:33.080
a second term in that body speaking to you on this occasion. Today I want to talk with you about

26:33.160 --> 26:40.520
some of the issues in the present senatorial campaign. I'm not going to indulge in a lot of

26:40.520 --> 26:46.920
recrimination and bickering back and forth. On my wall in the my Senate office in the Senate

26:46.920 --> 26:53.800
office building in Washington I have framed a very important saying of Abraham Lincoln and which

26:53.800 --> 26:59.400
he says that if I spend all of my time answering my bitter critics I wouldn't have time for public

26:59.480 --> 27:04.680
business and that's the way I feel about it. Any event it wouldn't be in a use trying to

27:06.360 --> 27:13.000
go into all of the charges and misrepresentations and innuendo that's being put around by one of

27:13.000 --> 27:19.800
my opponent, because he apparently changes his position from place to place and what he says in

27:19.800 --> 27:25.480
Tennessee does not always coincide with just what his record is in the Congress of the United

27:25.640 --> 27:31.640
States. Just as one example, now at Memphis Tennessee on the talkathon and I have the exact

27:32.120 --> 27:37.720
transcript here. One of my opponents when asked whether he was for universal military training said

27:37.720 --> 27:43.640
quote, I'm not for universal military training, I'm bitterly opposed to it and I'm conscientiously

27:43.640 --> 27:50.440
opposed to it. Then when asked if he didn't vote for it in 1951 he answered quote, I definitely

27:50.520 --> 27:55.640
did not. Well here happens to be the, that's what he said in Memphis Tennessee on the talkathon.

27:56.280 --> 28:00.440
Here happens to be the voting record on universal military training and service.

28:01.160 --> 28:07.640
S1, here's the motion to recommit, he voted against the motion to recommit, here's the vote for

28:07.640 --> 28:13.400
final passage of universal military training which he voted for, here's the conference report

28:13.400 --> 28:17.880
after differences have been worked out with the House of Representatives which he voted for,

28:18.440 --> 28:23.960
three very distinct votes so that I don't think there'd be any use with one who shifts his position

28:23.960 --> 28:29.800
from time to time and trying to follow the various and sundry shifts. So I want to talk about what

28:29.800 --> 28:35.880
I've tried to do and what I plan to do in the future. Friends as you know I was elected to the House

28:35.880 --> 28:42.440
of Representatives back in 1939 and then six years ago you elected me to the United States Senate.

28:43.320 --> 28:50.120
Since I have been there I have cast a vote on thousands and thousands of controversial issues.

28:51.240 --> 28:55.560
