years in dozens and dozens of cities we held hundreds of hearings exposing to the spotlight of

54:20.440 --> 54:25.800
public opinion. They racketeers, the dope peddlers, the big-time murderers, murdering,

54:25.800 --> 54:32.680
cooperated the big-time gamblers and the hoodlums of this nation. But the people of the nation saw

54:32.680 --> 54:38.520
sick and saddened them. Here these people taking billions and billions of dollars away from the

54:38.520 --> 54:47.960
American people in narcotics, gambling, theft of automobiles, killing for hire had gotten very very

54:47.960 --> 54:53.960
powerful in this nation. They were eating at the heart of our democracy. Many places they had taken

54:54.680 --> 55:01.080
over. Their influence was felt in many counties and cities, in states and even at the federal level.

55:01.720 --> 55:06.440
They were trying to control elections in many many places and they were successful in a lot of them.

55:07.320 --> 55:13.320
Well as a result of it we found also that with all of this money they were getting into all kinds

55:13.320 --> 55:19.880
of legitimate businesses, even great big transportation companies. And then these businesses

55:19.880 --> 55:25.960
they use the same gangster tactics of unfair competition, gangster methods that they did in

55:25.960 --> 55:30.760
their underworld life. But even more important than that we found that like termites they were

55:30.760 --> 55:36.280
warming their way into government and politics at all levels. But many places the good people didn't

55:36.280 --> 55:42.440
have a chance. Well we know that we can lose our democracy by corruption and and difference and

55:42.440 --> 55:48.360
crime within just as we can lose it by invasion from without. We know that nations which in their

55:48.360 --> 55:55.480
time were as great as we are in our time have a past away into into into third rate nations

55:55.480 --> 56:00.360
or have lost their influence in the world. The cost of indifference and the influence of the

56:00.360 --> 56:06.760
criminal and corruption within. And we simply do not want that to happen to the United States of

56:06.760 --> 56:12.680
America. As a result of our crime committee these gangs were exposed. They were broken up.

56:13.480 --> 56:21.160
As the people in New York and Philadelphia in Miami and Tampa and New Orleans in Cleveland and

56:21.160 --> 56:27.720
Detroit in Chicago in Kansas City, St. Louis, Los Angeles, San Francisco, what happened out there?

56:28.760 --> 56:35.240
We expose them. They have better law enforcement. Dozens and dozens of crime commissions have been

56:35.240 --> 56:40.600
formed. Better people are participating in government and we got the criminals on the run.

56:41.400 --> 56:47.640
Well as a result also of our crime investigating committee many very worthwhile federal laws were passed.

56:48.600 --> 56:52.680
The for instance one bill was passed to prohibit the interstate shipment of

56:53.480 --> 56:58.040
of our gambling devices from one state to the other which has had a very wholesome effect.

56:58.920 --> 57:03.720
It's interesting to note in passing that when that bill was up in the House of Representatives in

57:03.720 --> 57:11.800
August 1950, H.R. 807, that one of my opponents in this campaign offered an amendment to not

57:11.800 --> 57:20.200
allow the bill prohibiting the shipment of gambling devices to apply to any army camps or clubs

57:20.200 --> 57:25.000
or service men. Well the members of the Congress ridicule that saying do you want a different

57:25.000 --> 57:30.680
code of conduct? Do you want a different kind of morals for army camps and what not then you do

57:30.760 --> 57:38.120
for the rest of the public. So the amendment of my one of my opponents to this bill in which he tried

57:38.120 --> 57:45.640
to make this exemption was voted down at that time. State codes have been improved. There's been

57:45.640 --> 57:51.320
better law enforcement all over the United States. The hold of the gangster on this nation has been

57:51.320 --> 57:58.600
substantially broken and it will continue to be broken as long as we have an alert people who

57:58.600 --> 58:04.120
participate in government and see that the gangster doesn't get a hold on this. Well the back

58:04.120 --> 58:10.360
bone of this whole criminal organization in the United States, the thing that held it together

58:10.360 --> 58:16.520
from coast to coast, that kept the racketeers in touch with one another was the so-called continental

58:16.520 --> 58:22.760
wire service. That was the gambling wire service or the mob wire service as it's often called.

58:23.480 --> 58:31.400
It was owned by Mr. McBride, Mickey McBride of Cleveland, Ohio, and operated out of Chicago. Later

58:31.400 --> 58:37.400
Mr. McBride transferred a great deal of it to his son. They either got her stole information from

58:37.400 --> 58:44.040
the race tracks and put it on the wires instantly. It went out to hundreds and hundreds of sub-distributors

58:44.040 --> 58:50.120
and then from these sub-distributors to the gambling houses, the bookmakers, and to tens of

58:50.120 --> 58:55.400
thousands of people in all of the states of this union. It was around these gambling houses that

58:55.400 --> 59:03.480
other kinds of crime took place. That was a central figure, narcotics and murder and a feverate.

59:03.480 --> 59:10.040
It was around these sub-distributors that the mafia, this criminal underworld which we have broken

59:10.040 --> 59:16.520
up in this nation and which had such a powerful influence operated. This gambling wire service,

59:16.520 --> 59:22.520
we spent a great deal of time on. We exposed it for what it was and it had to go out of existence

59:22.520 --> 59:29.320
and Mr. McBride lost a very substantial investment in it. It is at least of passing interest to the

59:29.320 --> 59:38.200
people of Tennessee that Mr. McBride was a business partner with Mr. Robert G. Venn of Miami Florida.

59:38.200 --> 59:45.160
Mr. McBride and his associates owned a radio station there, WEMI in which Mr. Venn had an interest

59:45.160 --> 59:51.720
and was the general manager. Mr. Venn through this radio station constantly opposed the work of our

59:51.720 --> 59:58.120
crime committee. He also opposed the work of the greater Miami crime commission which was trying to

59:58.120 --> 01:00:05.960
get the hoodlums out of Miami. Here's the letter setting up the contract between Mr. McBride and Mr. Venn in

01:00:05.960 --> 01:00:16.040
August 1948. This is the first time that I have known of in Tennessee that a professional

01:00:16.040 --> 01:00:21.160
publicist who has come into the state to try to sell a political candidate. It's just like an

01:00:21.160 --> 01:00:27.640
advanced man for a carnival or selling soap. It's a little bit unusual that this man who has

01:00:27.640 --> 01:00:35.080
associated for so long and still is, as far as I know, with Mr. Arthur B. McBride's interest,

01:00:35.160 --> 01:00:40.680
should be the one to come into Tennessee to try to defeat me. Well undoubtedly, these have been

01:00:40.680 --> 01:00:46.840
many retaliations and threats of trying to take me out of public life. They're not on my side and

01:00:46.840 --> 01:00:52.760
I don't want them on my side. Look at some of these trucks holding around gambling devices in

01:00:52.760 --> 01:00:57.800
Tennessee. You'll see that they have a candidate for the United States Senate, all right, but that

01:00:57.800 --> 01:01:03.240
candidate is not Estus Keefer. I don't want them on my side and I will always fight this

01:01:04.040 --> 01:01:09.000
connection between crime and politics. I think that people of Tennessee are perfectly

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:14.680
capable of electing a United States Senator without the intervention of someone who would be

01:01:14.680 --> 01:01:19.320
inspired not to be very friendly because we put the mob wire service out of business.

01:01:20.360 --> 01:01:25.800
Well, among the other statutes that we got passed in the federal government as a result of our

01:01:26.760 --> 01:01:33.320
crime investigation was a mandatory sentence for dope peddlers and sellers after their first

01:01:33.320 --> 01:01:38.840
defense. And this has done a whole lot to clean up the narcotics condition in this country as Mr.

01:01:38.840 --> 01:01:45.800
Enzlinger, the head of the Bureau of Narcotics will tell you. Then we also recommended to the Congress

01:01:45.800 --> 01:01:51.480
and that the Immigration and Naturalization Act be amended so that we could deport some of

01:01:51.480 --> 01:01:57.080
these dozens and dozens of leading racketeers in this country who were the heads of some of these

01:01:57.080 --> 01:02:03.000
criminal centricates, many of them were naturalized Americans. And I don't think the United States

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:08.520
owes there many obligation to keep them here when they engage in terrible criminal activity.

01:02:09.400 --> 01:02:16.840
Well, the law was and it used to be very, very strict on deporting these people, but upon

01:02:16.840 --> 01:02:22.360
our recommendation the law was amended so that they could be deported if they committed some

01:02:22.360 --> 01:02:27.240
act of moral turpitude for which they were convicted within five years after they were admitted.

01:02:28.040 --> 01:02:34.920
Or if it was more than five years if they committed two acts. And the judge had to, and this would

01:02:34.920 --> 01:02:40.120
be true unless the judge at the time of the hearing, or they're in 30 days thereafter, recommended

01:02:40.120 --> 01:02:46.680
against deportation. Well, one of my opponents for some strange reason, I don't know what the,

01:02:46.680 --> 01:02:51.880
I don't know of any of these criminal aliens in Tennessee who were interested. They weren't

01:02:51.880 --> 01:03:01.640
any of them in Tennessee. On April 22, 1951, introduced a bill, HR 4794, which would allow the judge

01:03:01.640 --> 01:03:08.120
any time, any time up to deportation to recommend against deportation. This was taken up with the

01:03:08.120 --> 01:03:13.800
Attorney General of the United States who said that it would have the result of preventing the

01:03:13.800 --> 01:03:19.480
deportation of many alien criminals who ran this country and who ought to be deported. Well,

01:03:19.480 --> 01:03:27.320
that's a very interesting situation to develop. I don't know what people it was intended to prevent

01:03:27.320 --> 01:03:31.960
from being deported, but it certainly would have afforded the work of the Attorney General of the

01:03:31.960 --> 01:03:37.000
United States, and it would have afforded the recommendation of our Crime Commission Committee.

01:03:37.640 --> 01:03:43.720
Ladies and gentlemen, I think we must always keep America a clean nation, free from the influence of

01:03:43.720 --> 01:03:50.520
the recordiers and mobsters, and I'm going to keep on doing the best I can, regardless of what

01:03:50.520 --> 01:03:55.960
pressure our effort may be used against me and this campaign are in the future. Thank you very much.

01:03:56.200 --> 01:04:12.600
This is Esther's key for campaigning for the presidency. I want to talk with you about some of the

01:04:12.600 --> 01:04:18.280
vital issues of today. Today, let us talk about corruption. We have all been shocked and a little

01:04:18.280 --> 01:04:25.240
more terrified by the evidence of corruption at many levels of government in Washington, in some states,

01:04:25.240 --> 01:04:31.320
and in some cities. The situation must be cleaned up. Confidence in government must be fully

01:04:31.320 --> 01:04:37.880
restored. Politics must be made completely honest again. As president, I would make this my first

01:04:37.880 --> 01:04:43.320
order of business. Working together with the states and local governments and honest citizens

01:04:43.320 --> 01:04:49.240
everywhere, we can put the recordiers, the influence peddlers, and the pay chislers out of business,

01:04:49.880 --> 01:04:56.440
out of government, and cause their influence to be diminished in this country. We cannot face the

01:04:56.440 --> 01:05:02.600
perils of tomorrow unless we have absolute integrity all the way through our government at every level.

01:05:03.160 --> 01:05:12.840
Thank you very much for listening. I hope you will help me in my effort.

